Urban/Rural: Places with 50 000 or more inhabitants are usually considered urban in Korea. However the census results are composed in the basis of the minor administrative divisions such as Dongs (mostly urban areas) and Eups or Myeons (rural areas) rather than urban or rural residences. In this report urban refers to Dongs and rural refers to Eups and Myeons.
